    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="eyebrow">Partnerships</div>
        <h1>Helping families discover Berlin with babies.</h1>
        <p>
          Fix My Diaper is a community-driven local platform helping parents find changing tables,
          family-friendly places and activities — with practical information families can actually use.
        </p>
        <a class="text-link" href="mailto:hello@fixmydiaper.com?subject=Partnership%20with%20Fix%20My%20Diaper">
          Get in touch →
        </a>
      </section>

      <section class="section founder-grid">
        <div class="founder-photo">
          <img src="images/partnerships-founder.jpg" alt="Founder of Fix My Diaper in Berlin">
        </div>

        <div class="founder-copy">
          <h2>Built from a very real parenting problem.</h2>
          <p>
            Hi, I’m Fernanda. Becoming a parent completely changed the way I experience the city.
          </p>
          <p>
            Before having a baby, I never noticed whether a café had a changing table, whether a bathroom could fit a stroller,
            or whether a place was truly welcoming to families.
          </p>
          <p>
            Suddenly, these details shaped every outing. Fix My Diaper was created to make that information visible:
            a practical map and discovery platform built by parents, for parents.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-title">Who we reach</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">
            A growing Berlin-based audience of parents looking for useful, trustworthy local recommendations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-4">
          <div class="card metric">
            <strong>Primarily women</strong>
            <span>Parents and caregivers making everyday family decisions.</span>
          </div>

          <div class="card metric">
            <strong>Babies & toddlers</strong>
            <span>Families in the stage where accessibility matters most.</span>
          </div>

          <div class="card metric">
            <strong>Germany-based</strong>
            <span>With a strong and growing focus on Berlin.</span>
          </div>

          <div class="card metric">
            <strong>Local discovery</strong>
            <span>People actively deciding where to go next.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-title">What we create</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">
            Useful content that helps families decide where to go, what to try and what to trust.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-3">
          <div class="card large">
            <h3>Instagram Guides</h3>
            <p>Saveable recommendations that help parents discover places worth visiting.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card large">
            <h3>Neighbourhood Guides</h3>
            <p>Practical local guides for families exploring Berlin by area.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card large">
            <h3>Interactive Map</h3>
            <p>A tool that helps parents find changing tables and baby-friendly places nearby.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card large">
            <h3>Reels & Stories</h3>
            <p>Short, honest content showing real places and real family-friendly details.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card large">
            <h3>Curated Recommendations</h3>
            <p>Places, services and events that fit naturally into everyday family life.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card large">
            <h3>Future Newsletter</h3>
            <p>A direct channel for guides, family events and trusted local recommendations.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-title">How we work</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">
            We do not create traditional ads. We create useful local context.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-3 process">
          <div class="card large">
            <h3>We visit</h3>
            <p>We look at the details families care about: changing tables, stroller access, atmosphere and practical comfort.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card large">
            <h3>We create useful content</h3>
            <p>Your place becomes part of a recommendation that genuinely helps parents plan their day.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card large">
            <h3>Families discover you</h3>
            <p>Parents find you through guides, stories, recommendations and the map — when they are already looking for where to go.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-title">Success Stories</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">
            A reusable format for collaborations, guides and local discovery stories.
          </p>
        </div>

        <article class="success-story">
          <div class="success-top">
            <div class="success-title-card">
              <h3>Neukölln Family Guide</h3>
              <p>
                A neighbourhood guide designed to help parents discover practical, welcoming places in Neukölln —
                from cafés to baby-friendly stops and useful local recommendations.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="screenshot-placeholder">
              Space for Reel / carousel / guide screenshot
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="story-details">
            <div class="card">
              <h3>Challenge</h3>
              <p>Parents often hear that an area is family-friendly, but still do not know which places are practical with a baby.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h3>Content created</h3>
              <p>A curated guide with real local recommendations, useful context and places families can save for later.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h3>Results</h3>
              <p>Space to add reach, saves, shares, website clicks, profile visits or partner inquiries.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h3>Community response</h3>
              <p>Space to add DMs, comments, parent recommendations and follow-up submissions.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h3>Partner visibility</h3>
              <p>Partners appear inside useful recommendations, making the mention feel natural and relevant.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
              <h3>Reusable format</h3>
              <p>The same structure can be used for cafés, hotels, events, museums, family spaces and neighbourhood guides.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-title">Why brands collaborate with us</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">
            Because families do not need more ads. They need better recommendations.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-block">
          <p>
            Collaborations are always integrated naturally into content that helps families make better decisions.
            A café, hotel, store or family space is not simply promoted — it becomes part of a useful recommendation.
          </p>
          <p>
            Parents are looking for honest, practical information: Is there space for a stroller?
            Is there a changing table? Is this place worth leaving the house for?
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="section-header">
          <h2 class="section-title">Ideal partners</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">
            We work best with places and brands that genuinely make family life easier, warmer or more fun.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid grid-3">
          <div class="card"><h3>Family cafés</h3><p>Places where parents can feel welcome, not like an inconvenience.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Play cafés</h3><p>Spaces designed around children, connection and everyday family life.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Baby stores</h3><p>Useful products and local shops parents are already looking for.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Hotels</h3><p>Family-friendly stays, city trips and practical travel recommendations.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Museums</h3><p>Places helping families experience culture with babies and young children.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Libraries</h3><p>Accessible, calm and community-oriented places for families.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Family events</h3><p>Local activities parents can actually plan around.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Workshops</h3><p>Classes, meetups and experiences for parents, babies and toddlers.</p></div>
          <div class="card"><h3>Parent services</h3><p>Local services that support families in practical, meaningful ways.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <div class="contact-box">
          <h2>Let’s build something useful.</h2>
          <p>
            Interested in collaborating? Reach out even if you have never worked with creators or local platforms before.
            We can keep it simple, thoughtful and genuinely helpful for families.
          </p>

          <a class="contact-button" href="mailto:hello@fixmydiaper.com?subject=Partnership%20with%20Fix%20My%20Diaper">
            hello@fixmydiaper.com
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
